d%20be%20hurting%20some%20workers'%20productivity.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EWhen%20we%20see%20incivility%2C%20even%20secondhand%2C%20it%20can%20hijack%20our%20attention%20and%20focus%2C%20an%20expert%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EOne%20boss%20is%20considering%20letting%20his%20employees%20work%20remotely%20in%20the%20weeks%20after%20the%20election.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EAJ%20Gareffa%20thought%20about%20taking%20off%20the%20day%20after%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felon-musk-donald-trump-support-reflects-business-approach-tesla-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETuesday's%20election%3C%2Fa%3E%20but%20instead%20plans%20to%20be%20off%20work%20for%20the%20entire%20week.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGareffa%2C%2027%2C%20is%20a%20therapist%20in%20Livonia%2C%20Michigan%2C%20near%20Detroit.%20They%20said%20they've%20already%20found%20in%20recent%20days%20that%20stress%20over%20the%20election%20is%20causing%20their%20mind%20to%20sometimes%20wander%20for%20a%20few%20seconds%20when%20they're%20with%20a%20client.%20Gareffa%20said%20that's%20a%20sign%20that%20time%20off%20is%20needed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20can't%20be%20a%20life%20raft%20to%20anyone%20if%20you%20are%20drowning%2C%26quot%3B%20they%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221818%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22AJ%20Gareffa%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6725522501ea6d83dee5c21e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221364%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAJ%20Gareffa%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20Macey%20Caffrey%20Photography%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EGareffa%20isn't%20alone%20in%20finding%20it%20harder%20to%20concentrate%20at%20work%20because%20of%20anxiety%20over%20the%20election.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20survey%20of%201%2C000%20US%20managers%20conducted%20online%20in%20October%20by%20ResumeBuilder.com%2C%2038%25%20of%20respondents%20said%20the%20election%20had%20already%20hurt%20morale%20and%20productivity.%20Seven%20in%2010%20managers%20are%20worried%20tensions%20will%20worsen%20after%20the%20election.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFelix%20Kim%20is%20the%20founder%20and%20CEO%20of%20Redrob%2C%20a%20startup%20that%20develops%20skills%20assessments%20designed%20to%20remove%20bias%20from%20hiring.%20He%20is%20concerned%2C%20in%20part%2C%20that%20the%20election%20might%20hurt%20team%20cohesion%20and%20said%20he's%20already%20seeing%20signs%20that%20the%20inescapable%20campaign%20news%20is%20wearing%20on%20workers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPeople%2C%20of%20course%2C%20are%20distracted%2C%26quot%3B%20Kim%20said.%20He%20said%20he's%20planning%20for%20disruptions%20to%20his%20company's%20routines%20because%2C%20no%20matter%20who%20wins%2C%20%26quot%3Bit's%20going%20to%20be%20a%20wild%20ride.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKim%20is%20considering%20telling%20the%20small%20company's%20workers%20who%20normally%20commute%20to%20its%20office%20in%20New%20York%20City%20several%20days%20a%20week%20to%20work%20remotely%20following%20the%20election%2C%20perhaps%20for%20as%20long%20as%20two%20weeks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22e1c91231-8a67-4773-82bc-1feb19ee349c%5C%22%3EThe%20cost%20of%20tension%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20American%20Psychological%20Association%20found%20in%20an%20August%20survey%20that%20nearly%20seven%20in%2010%20US%20adults%20reported%20that%20the%20election%20was%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.apa.org%2Fpubs%2Freports%2Fstress-in-america%2F2024%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%26quot%3Bsignificant%26quot%3B%20source%20of%20stress%3C%2Fa%3E.%20That's%20similar%20to%202020%20and%20above%20the%2052%25%20of%20adults%20who%20reported%20the%20same%20level%20of%20anxiety%20in%202016.%20The%20online%20survey%2C%20conducted%20by%20The%20Harris%20Poll%20on%20behalf%20of%20the%20APA%2C%20involved%20about%203%2C300%20adults%20in%20the%20US.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20emotional%20drain%20of%20what%20we're%20all%20experiencing%20is%20going%20to%20lower%20productivity%2C%26quot%3B%20Gabriella%20Kellerman%2C%20chief%20innovation%20officer%20at%20the%20virtual%20coaching%20platform%20BetterUp%2C%20told%20BI.%20How%20much%20we%20get%20done%20on%20the%20job%20can%20drop%20because%20of%20our%20own%20anxiety%2C%20and%20when%20working%20with%20others%20becomes%20fraught.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAs%20we%20get%20closer%20to%20the%20election%2C%20people%20are%20more%20likely%20to%20avoid%20coworkers%20based%20on%20feared%20political%20tension%2C%26quot%3B%20Kellerman%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20friction%2C%20or%20fear%20of%20it%2C%20can%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjob-politics-talking-discussions-work-rules-election-hr-trump-harris-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehurt%20team%20output%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDorie%20Clark%2C%20a%20communication%20coach%20who%20teaches%20at%20Columbia%20Business%20School%20and%20is%20the%20author%20of%20%26quot%3BThe%20Long%20Game%2C%26quot%3B%20told%20BI%20that%20some%20workers%20have%20been%20preoccupied%20for%20months%20about%20the%20election.%20That's%20likely%20to%20increase%20on%20Election%20Day%2C%20and%20perhaps%20in%20its%20aftermath%2C%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20said%20some%20workers%20will%20be%20busy%20hitting%20refresh%20on%20news%20and%20social%20sites%2C%20looking%20for%20insight%20into%20how%20the%20election%20might%20swing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhat%20they're%20wanting%20is%20the%20one%20thing%20they%20can't%20have%2C%20which%20is%20control%2C%26quot%3B%20Clark%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20said%20that%20for%20some%20workers%2C%20not%20knowing%20what%20their%20future%20%E2%80%94%20and%20that%20of%20the%20country%20%E2%80%94might%20look%20like%20because%20of%20the%20vote%20can%20produce%20major%20stress.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20is%20not%20dissimilar%20to%20a%20patient%20who%20has%20acute%20symptoms%20but%20no%20diagnosis%2C%26quot%3B%20Clark%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%229ea62c69-07ec-4729-82df-cad4d8874b26%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EBad%20behavior%20can%20be%20contagious%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EChristine%20Porath%2C%20a%20professor%20at%20the%20University%20of%20North%20Carolina%20at%20Chapel%20Hill's%20Kenan-Flagler%20Business%20School%20and%20author%20of%20%26quot%3BMastering%20Community%2C%26quot%3B%20told%20BI%20that%20the%20toxicity%20of%20a%20divisive%20election%20could%20seep%20into%20our%20workdays%20as%20people%20are%20exposed%20to%20rudeness%20and%20bad%20behavior%20%E2%80%94%20even%20if%20they're%20only%20learning%20about%20it%20secondhand.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20very%20distracting%20and%20hijacks%20our%20attention%20and%20focus.%20It%20leads%20us%20to%20perform%20worse%2C%20be%20far%20less%20creative%2C%20less%20helpful%20to%20others%2C%20and%20unfortunately%2C%20it%20is%20contagious%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPorath%20said%20that%20when%20incivility%20infiltrates%20the%20workplace%2C%20it%20primes%20employees%20to%20act%20or%20think%20dysfunctionally.%20Those%20employees%2C%20in%20turn%2C%20can%20spread%20that%20negativity%20to%20their%20coworkers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Society%20for%20Human%20Resource%20Management%20reports%20that%20politics%20is%20a%20%26quot%3Btop%20driver%26quot%3B%20of%20incivility%20on%20the%20job.%20Discourtesy%2C%20the%20organization%20said%2C%20costs%20US%20organizations%20a%20collective%20%242.17%20billion%20every%20day%20due%20to%20absenteeism%20and%20reduced%20productivity.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYet%20it's%20not%20all%20bad%20news.%20In%20research%20Porath%20conducted%20several%20years%20ago%20involving%20six%20organizations%20in%20different%20industries%2C%20she%20found%20that%20workers%20who%20felt%20that%20they%20were%20thriving%20in%20their%20jobs%20were%20better%20able%20to%20repel%20the%20type%20of%20negativity%20%E2%80%94%20like%20that%20emanating%20from%20a%20contentious%20election%20%E2%80%94%20that%20could%20lead%20them%20to%20become%20distracted.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%228d93d8a3-d2e2-42f2-8755-79681440a7c4%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20managers%20can%20do%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EClark%2C%20the%20communication%20coach%2C%20said%20managers%20shouldn't%20make%20assumptions%20about%20their%20teams'%20political%20leanings%20but%20should%20instead%20be%20sensitive%20to%20employees'%20emotions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYet%20that%20doesn't%20mean%20being%20overly%20indulgent%20or%20letting%20workers%20focus%20too%20long%20on%20issues%20that%20aren't%20germane%20to%20the%20business.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20might%20feel%20sad%20about%20who%20wins%20or%20loses%20a%20presidential%20election%2C%20but%20this%20is%20very%20different%20than%2C%20say%2C%20the%20death%20of%20a%20relative%2C%26quot%3B%20Clark%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20the%20widespread%20election%20worries%2C%20not%20every%20indicator%20signals%20that%20the%20vexing%20political%20climate%20is%20throwing%20off%20most%20workers.%20In%20an%20online%20survey%20of%20about%20900%20US%20workers%20conducted%20from%20late%20August%20to%20mid-September%2C%20the%20research%20firm%20Gartner%20found%20that%20while%2048%25%20of%20employees%20said%20they%20were%20anxious%20about%20who%20would%20win%20the%20election%2C%20two-thirds%20of%20respondents%20said%20those%20concerns%20hadn't%20dented%20their%20productivity%20at%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGareffa%2C%20the%20therapist%20in%20Michigan%2C%20doesn't%20want%20to%20risk%20being%20overly%20distracted%20when%20they're%20with%20clients.%20Gareffa%20plans%20to%20use%20the%20week%20off%20from%20work%20to%20spend%20time%20with%20family%20and%20perhaps%20focus%20on%20a%20hobby%20like%20drawing%20or%20sculpting.%20They%20said%20their%20clients%20have%20been%20understanding%20about%20the%20planned%20time%20away.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20been%20a%20good%20kind%20of%20example%20of%20how%20to%20take%20care%20of%20yourself%20without%20just%20running%20away%20from%20responsibilities%20or%20just%20pumping%20the%20brakes%20on%20life%2C%26quot%3B%20Gareffa%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-election-cutting-into-some-worker-productivity-2024-11%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1730541782000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6722729001ea6d83dee52544%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-election-cutting-into-some-worker-productivity-2024-11%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Election%20stress%20can%20impact%20workers'%20productivity.%20One%20expert%20says%20managers%20should%20be%20sensitive%20to%20political%20tensions%2C%20but%20shouldn't%20be%20overindulgent.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22tparadis%40businessinsider.com%20(Tim%20Paradis)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-election-cutting-into-some-worker-productivity-2024-11%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Charged%20Rs%20100%20cr%20for%20advising%20political%20parties%2C%20reveals%20Prashant%20Kishor%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1730541765000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fpolitics%2Fcharged-rs-100-cr-for-advising-political-parties-reveals-prashant-kishor-124110200553_1.html%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Prashant%20Kishor%20said%20that%2010%20state%20governments%20currently%20employ%20his%20strategies%2C%20while%20adding%20that%20he%20has%20ample%20resources%20to%20fund%20his%20campaign%20needs%20in%20Bihar%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22World's%20largest%20crocodile%20in%20captivity%20dies%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1730541750000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fichef.bbci.co.uk%2Fnews%2F1024%2Fbranded_news%2F75a7%2Flive%2F5c7f1b40-98f8-11ef-9260-19e6a950e830.jpg%22%2C%22or