3E%3C%2Fsection%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%3Cp%3EBI%20combed%20through%20over%20600%20reader%20responses%20to%20the%20survey%20and%20over%20150%20emails%20to%20discern%20four%20main%20frustrations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22d7db38df-e97e-4bc5-a2b4-44851ec00610%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EOlder%20Americans%20are%20struggling%20to%20find%20work%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EFritz%20Boyle%2C%2055%2C%20has%20been%20looking%20for%20roles%20as%20a%20user%20experience%20strategist%20in%20AI%20and%20software%20development%20since%20he%20was%20laid%20off%20last%20year.%20He%20said%20he's%20landed%20several%20interviews%20and%20made%20it%20to%20the%20final%20round%20twice%2C%20but%20he%20hasn't%20received%20an%20offer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20believe%20I%20am%20suffering%20from%20ageism%2C%20and%20much%20younger%2C%20cheaper%20candidates%20are%20getting%20the%20positions%20I%20have%20been%20applying%20to%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Boyle%2C%20who%20lives%20in%20Portland%2C%20Oregon.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAbout%20half%20of%20the%20total%20respondents%20were%20over%20the%20age%20of%2050.%20Over%20a%20dozen%20respondents%20also%20said%20they%20couldn't%20find%20roles%20that%20paid%20the%20same%20as%20previous%20positions%20and%2C%20therefore%2C%20settled%20for%20lower-paying%20jobs%2C%20which%20delayed%20their%20retirement%20plans.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20many%20who%20still%20haven't%20found%20work%2C%20their%20finances%20are%20taking%20a%20hit.%20Over%20three%20dozen%20respondents%20said%20they%20pulled%20from%20their%20401(k)%20or%20IRAs%20to%20stay%20afloat.%20A%20few%20dozen%20baby%20boomer%20and%20Gen%20X%20respondents%20who%20were%20recently%20laid%20off%20said%20they%20went%20into%20debt%20for%20the%20first%20time%20or%20relocated%20to%20a%20lower-cost%20area.%20A%20few%20said%20they%20have%20declared%20or%20are%20considering%20declaring%20bankruptcy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20be%20sure%2C%20while%20many%20older%20job%20seekers%20said%20their%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eage%20is%20a%20challenge%2C%20Bureau%20of%20Labor%20Statistics%20data%20shows%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ffred.stlouisfed.org%2Fseries%2FLNU04000095%230%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eunemployment%20rate%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20those%20between%2055%20and%2064%20has%20persistently%20been%20lower%20than%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ffred.stlouisfed.org%2Fseries%2FUNRATENSA%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enational%20rate%3C%2Fa%3E.%20One%20explanation%20for%20this%20is%20that%20older%20workers%20drop%20in%20and%20out%20of%20job%20searches%20%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%94%20%3C%2Fspan%3Eand%20thus%20the%20pool%20of%20unemployed%20workers%20as%20defined%20by%20BLS%20%E2%80%94%20taking%20the%20time%20to%20network%20or%20find%20the%20right%20opportunity%2C%20said%20economist%20Aaron%20Terrazas.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22d6a060cb-09d7-49e7-8eed-0a98875ed0cb%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EIncreased%20competition%20and%20AI%20are%20fueling%20frustrations%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EDozens%20of%20respondents%20across%20all%20generations%20said%20they%20were%20frustrated%20by%20the%20number%20of%20people%20who%20applied%20for%20the%20roles%20they%20wanted%20on%20platforms%20like%20LinkedIn%2C%20which%20shows%20whether%20jobs%20are%20popular%20among%20applicants.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20LinkedIn%20analysis%20of%20August%20data%20for%20eight%20countries%2C%20including%20the%20US%2C%20showed%20that%20competition%20for%20roles%20across%20eight%20industries%20is%20higher%20than%20two%20years%20ago%20%E2%80%94%20including%20professional%20services%2C%20financial%20services%2C%20and%20accommodation%20and%20food%20services.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOver%20three%20dozen%20respondents%2C%20predominantly%20in%20their%2030s%20and%2040s%2C%20said%20they're%20confused%20about%20how%20to%20stand%20out%20amid%20the%20crowded%20fields%2C%20especially%20as%20many%20companies%20use%20AI%20to%20screen%20candidate's%20applications.%20Some%20paid%20to%20have%20their%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9s%20and%20cover