0said%20their%20credentials%20may%20have%20prevented%20them%20from%20getting%20interviews%20for%20lower-paying%20white-collar%20roles.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEmployment%20in%20professional%20and%20business%20services%2C%20which%20includes%20industries%20like%20legal%20and%20advertising%2C%20has%20cooled%20down%20in%20recent%20months%2C%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eper%20data%20from%20the%20Bureau%20of%20Labor%20Statistics.%20The%20information%20sector%2C%20which%20includes%20many%20tech%20roles%2C%20has%20also%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eseen%20weak%20employment%20changes%20this%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20try%20to%20regain%20an%20edge%20in%20the%20competitive%20market%2C%20a%20few%20dozen%20respondents%2C%20predominantly%20in%20their%2030s%20and%2040s%2C%20returned%20to%20school%20for%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcollege-worth-it-genx-six-figure-salary-paid-student-debt-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eadvanced%20degree%3C%2Fa%3E.%20While%20some%20said%20they%20valued%20those%20degrees%2C%20others%20cautioned%20that%20getting%20an%20MBA%20or%20a%20master's%20from%20higher-ranked%20universities%20didn't%20have%20noticeable%20results%20for%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStephanie%20Allen%2C%2053%2C%20has%20been%20seeking%20writing%20and%20customer%20service%20jobs%20since%20March%202023.%20She%20said%20her%20education%20has%20sometimes%20hindered%20her%20search.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20believe%20having%20a%20master's%20degree%20in%20English%20turns%20off%20prospective%20employers%20because%20they%20don't%20believe%20that%20I'll%20stay%20at%20the%20position%20and%20will%20want%20something%20more%20challenging%20and%20higher%20paying%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20the%20Maryland%20resident.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYounger%20respondents%20also%20said%20they're%20struggling%20to%20secure%20roles%20in%20the%20corporate%20world%20after%20graduating.%20Over%20a%20dozen%20respondents%20in%20their%2020s%20said%20that%2C%20even%20with%20degrees%20fro