0ready%20to%20make%20a%20move%2C%20they%20can%20still%20save%20on%20taxes%20with%20the%20right%20lawyer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20creating%20a%20special%20kind%20of%20trust%2C%20business%20owners%20can%20take%20advantage%20of%20the%20loose%20tax%20laws%20of%20other%20states.%20Instead%20of%20selling%20a%20business%20outright%2C%20they%20transfer%20their%20shares%20to%20an%20incomplete%20non-grantor%20trust%20set%20up%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-states-tax-haven-billions-hidden-untaxed-wealth-assets-2022-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etax-haven%20state%3C%2Fa%3E%20such%20as%20Nevada.%20When%20the%20shares%20are%20sold%2C%20the%20trust%20collects%20the%20proceeds%20without%20paying%20any%20state%20income%20or%20capital-gains%20taxes.%20The%20trust%20assets%20grow%20free%20of%20those%20taxes%20and%20are%20shielded%20from%20creditors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDan%20Griffith%20of%20Huntington%20Bank%20expects%20ING%20trusts%20will%20surge%20in%20popularity%20with%20dealmaking%20on%20the%20rebound%20coinciding%20with%20a%20%26quot%3Bsilver%20tsunami.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou've%20got%20baby-boomer%20business%20owners%20who%20need%20to%20transition%2C%20and%20you%20also%20have%20a%20ton%20of%20capital%20on%20the%20sidelines%20looking%20for%20transactions%2C%26quot%3B%20Griffith%2C%20Huntington's%20director%20of%20wealth%20strategy%2C%20said.%20%26quot%3BWith%20more%20deals%20comes%20more%20need%20for%20tax-saving%20strategies.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInvestors%20can%20also%20benefit%20from%20putting%20their%20portfolios%20in%20ING%20trusts%20because%20that%20allows%20the%20dividends%20to%20grow%20free%20of%20state%20taxes.%20ING%20trusts%20are%20powerful%20tax-avoidance%20tools%2C%20so%20much%20so%20that%20New%20York%20and%20California%20have%20enacted%20laws%20to%20render%20them%20useless%20for%20state%20residents.%20California%20closed%20the%20loophole%20in%202023%2C%20estimating%20it%20would%20increase%20tax%20revenue%20by%20%2430%20million%20that%20year%20and%20%2417%20million%20each%20following%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEach%20state%20also%20has%20its%20own%20provisions%20to%20navigate%2C%20which%20makes%20setting%20up%20INGs%20cumbersome.%20However%2C%20Bank%20of%20America's%20Timothy%20Herbst%20said%20it%20could%20still%20be%20worth%20it%20in%20states%20without%20sky-high%20income-tax%20rates.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat%20trust%20can%20grow%20conceivably%20without%20any%20state%20income%20tax%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20wealth-strategy%20executive%20said.%20%26quot%3BThat's%20a%20significant%20savings%20even%20in%20a%20state%20like%20North%20Carolina%20at%204.5%25.%20It's%20not%20necessarily%20a%20huge%20income%20tax%2C%20but%20you%20look%20at%20a%20very%20large%20portfolio%20growing%20over%20decades%2C%20that%20can%20be%20real%20significant%20savings.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22a0857d85-806e-4e72-a9da-646cab9ef538%5C%22%3EHere%20is%20how%20ING%20trusts%20work%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EING%20trusts%20come%20in%20different%20flavors.%20Nevada%20and%20Delaware%20are%20popular%20states%20for%20domiciling%20ING%20trusts%2C%20where%20they're%20referred%20to%20as%20%26quot%3BNINGs%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3BDINGs%2C%26quot%3B%20respectively.%20However%2C%20Wyoming%20and%20South%20Dakota%20are%20also%20options%20as%20they%20do%20not%20tax%20trust%20income%20or%20capital%20gains%20and%20protect%20trust%20assets%20from%20creditors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20person%20who%20creates%20the%20trust%2C%20otherwise%20known%20as%20the%20settlor%2C%20does%20not%20have%20to%20reside%20in%20that%20state%2C%20but%20the%20trust%20should%20be%20administered%20by%20a%20third%20party%20who%20does.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHere's%20an%20example%20of%20how%20an%20ING%20trust%20can%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cblockquote%3E%3Csection%3EConsider%20a%20business%20owner%20in%20Oregon%20looking%20to%20sell%20a%20business%20worth%20%2450%20million%20that%20was%20worth%20barely%20%241%20million%20when%20it%20was%20founded.%20Oregon%20taxes%20income%20and%20capital%20gains%20at%209.9%25%20for%20top%20earners.%20If%20the%20owner%20sold%20their%20shares%20outright%2C%20they%20would%20be%20on%20the%20hook%20for%20%244.8%20million%20in%20taxes.%20Instead%2C%20they%20transfer%20their%20shares%20to%20an%20ING%20trust%20in%20Nevada.%20When%20the%20business%20is%20sold%2C%20the%20trust%20is%20spared%20those%20income%20taxes.%20The%20remainder%2C%20after%20federal%20capital-gains%20taxes%2C%20can%20be%20invested%20and%20grow%20free%20of%20state%20and%20local%20taxes.%3C%2Fsection%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%3Cp%3EING%20trusts%20are%20still%20subject%20to%20federal%20capital%20gains%20taxes%2C%20but%20the%20ultrawealthy%20users%20of%20INGs%20would%20likely%20be%20subject%20to%20that%20burden%20anyway.%20For%20a%20centimillionaire%2C%20it's%20not%20hard%20to%20reach%20the%20top%20rate%20of%2037%25%2C%20which%20applies%20to%20incomes%20above%20%24578%2C126.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThese%20are%20superrich%20people%2C%26quot%3B%20Bob%20Lord%2C%20a%20senior%20advisor%20on%20tax%20policy%20for%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpatriotic-millionaires-want-wealth-tax-congress-reconciliation-build-back-better-2022-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPatriotic%20Millionaires%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20said.%20%26quot%3BThey're%20still%20taking%20in%20enough%20to%20get%20to%20the%2037%25%20bracket.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFurthermore%2C%20INGs%20can%20be%20used%20to%20take%20advantage%20of%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fqsbs-qualified-small-business-stock-startups-criteria-taxes-2019-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etax%20perk%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20early%20shareholders%20that%20exempts%20at%20least%20%2410%20million%20in%20profits%20from%20the%20federal%20capital-gains%20tax.%20Steve%20Oshins%2C%20a%20Nevada%20lawyer%2C%20said%20founders%20could%20double%20their%20exemption%20by%20setting%20up%20an%20ING%20trust.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20trust%20can%20serve%20as%20a%20second%20taxpayer%20so%20that%20the%20individual%20can%20get%20a%20second%20%2410%20million%20exemption%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BThis%20can%20apply%20even%20if%20they%20don't%20live%20in%20a%20state%20with%20a%20state%20income%20tax.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20the%20ING%20trust%20to%20pass%20muster%20with%20state%20authorities%2C%20there%20should%20be%20multiple%20beneficiaries%20in%20addition%20to%20the%20settlor%20and%20their%20spouse.%20Since%20beneficiaries%20do%20have%20to%20pay%20state%20income%20taxes%20%E2%80%94%20if%20applicable%20%E2%80%94%20when%20they%20receive%20distributions.%20For%20this%20reason%2C%20lawyers%20advise%20that%20clients%20take%20as%20few%20distributions%20as%20possible%20and%20let%20the%20assets%20grow%20in%20the%20trust%20for%20their%20children%20or%20future%20generations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20is%20usually%20better%20that%20the%20client%20knows%20that%20distributions%20won't%20be%20coming%20back%20to%20him%20or%20her%20or%20to%20their%20spouse%2C%26quot%3B%20Herbst%20said.%20%26quot%3BIf%20they%20did%20need%20those%20distributions%2C%20then%20it%20probably%20is%20not%20going%20to%20be%20the%20right%20strategy.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20said%2C%20sometimes%20taking%20a%20distribution%20makes%20sense%20if%20there%20is%20financial%20need%20or%20the%20client%20has%20moved%20to%20a%20low-tax%20state%20since%20setting%20up%20the%20ING%20trust%2C%20Oshins%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20just%20have%20to%20look%20at%20each%20fact%20pattern%20on%20its%20own%20and%20make%20the%20right%20decision%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2268a845c4-1176-4c9e-871e-cd1aab5eb265%5C%22%3EBuyer%20beware%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Col%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EING%20trusts%20can't%20be%20used%20to%20avoid%20state%20taxes%20on%20salaries%20or%20rental%20income.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Fol%3E%3Cp%3EING%20trusts%20cannot%20be%20used%20to%20defer%20income%20taxes%20on%20salaries%20or%20income%20from%20tangible%20assets%20in%20the%20state.%20That%20income%2C%20referred%20to%20as%20source%20income%2C%20is%20subject%20to%20state%20taxes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20instance%2C%20Griffith%20said%2C%20an%20Ohio%20resident%20cannot%20avoid%20state%20or%20local%20taxes%20on%20income%20from%20rental%20properties%20in%20the%20state%20even%20if%20they%20transfer%20ownership%20of%20the%20properties%20to%20an%20ING%20trust%20in%20South%20Dakota.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20clients%20in%20states%20with%20aggressive%20tax%20authorities%2C%20Griffith%20recommends%20they%20step%20away%20from%20their%20business'%20day-to-day%20operations%20and%20collect%20a%20minimal%20salary%20before%20transferring%20their%20interests%20to%20the%20ING%20trust.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhat%20you%20really%20need%20to%20do%20is%20become%20essentially%20just%20a%20shareholder%2C%20be%2C%20as%20a%20business%20owner%2C%20somebody%20who%20says%2C%20'I%20am%20just%20receiving%20dividends%20from%20this%20company.%20I%20own%20C-corp%20stock%2C'%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BIn%20many%20states%2C%20that%20becomes%20non-source%20income.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Col%20start%3D%5C%222%5C%22%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3ESetting%20up%20an%20ING%20trust%20is%20like%20threading%20a%20needle.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Fol%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20trusts%20have%20to%20be%20structured%20carefully%20to%20avoid%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freal-estate-gift-tax-avoidance-trusts-wealth-planning-rich-inheritance-2023-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etriggering%20estate%20taxes%20of%20as%20much%20as%2040%25%3C%2Fa%3E%20while%20keeping%20the%20income-tax%20advantages.%20In%20addition%20to%20navigating%20the%20laws%20in%20the%20home%20state%20and%20the%20tax-haven%20state%2C%20the%20settlor%20has%20to%20retain%20certain%20rights%20and%20relinquish%20others.%20For%20instance%2C%20the%20settlor%20can't%20have%20the%20ability%20to%20compel%20distributions%20but%20should%20have%20the%20right%20to%20name%20beneficiaries%20at%20death.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20inherently%20complicated%2C%26quot%3B%20Griffith%20said.%20%26quot%3BYou've%20got%20to%20have%20a%20fairly%20sizable%20transaction%20to%20make%20the%20juice%20worth%20the%20squeeze.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Col%20start%3D%5C%223%5C%22%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20trust%20has%20to%20be%20set%20up%20well%20before%20the%20business%20is%20sold.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Fol%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20easier%20for%20a%20state%20tax%20authority%20to%20pursue%20income%20from%20the%20sale%20of%20a%20business%20if%20it%20is%20done%20shortly%20after%20the%20ING%20trust%20is%20established.%20Griffith%20recommends%20at%20least%20a%20year's%20delay%2C%20but%20it%20is%20the%20biggest%20challenge%20for%20clients%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey're%20like%2C%20'Oh%2C%20I%20don't%20want%20to%20fund%20the%20trust%20until%20we%20know%20we're%20going%20to%20sell.'%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BYou%20have%20to%20do%20it%20in%20advance.%20And%20if%20you%20do%2C%20those%20are%20the%20ones%20that%20I've%20seen%20that%20have%20been%20really%20successful.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frich-income-tax-capital-gains-ing-trust-nevada-delaware-2024-10%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1730538002000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6722a8739b3250dbbceb4d20%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frich-income-tax-capital-gains-ing-trust-nevada-delaware-2024-10%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Rich%20business%20owners%20looking%20to%20cash%20out%20can%20save%20big%20on%20income%20taxes%20by%20setting%20up%20trusts%20in%20tax-haven%20states%20without%20moving.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22hcuccinello%40businessinsider.com%20(Hayley%20Cuccinello)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A30%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frich-income-tax-capital-gains-ing-trust-nevada-delaware-2024-10%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22'The%20reversion%20will%20eventually%20come'%3A%20A%20chief%20strategist%20says%20Goldman%20Sachs%20and%20JPMorgan%20are%20right%20to%20warn%20of%20weak%20returns%20for%20the%20S%26amp%3BP%20500%20over%20the%20next%20decade%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22trader%20stunned%20shocked%20surprised%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5afeee0a1ae66225008b46e2%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221333%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EGetty%20Images%20%2F%20Spencer%20Platt%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EGoldman%20Sachs%20and%20JPMorgan%20predict%20relatively%20muted%20S%26amp%3BP%20500%20returns%20over%20the%20next%20decade.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ERIA%20Advisors'%20Lance%20Roberts%20says%20the%20banks%20are%20right.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHigh%20valuations%20and%20potential%20inflation%20could%20lead%20to%20lower%20stock-market%20returns%2C%20Roberts%20says.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EMuch%20has%20been%20said%20about%20the%20gloomy%20outlook%20for%20the%20S%26amp%3BP%20500%20that%20some%20of%20Wall%20Street's%20largest%20investment%20banks%20conveyed%20in%20recent%20weeks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fstocks%2Fstock-market-outlook-sp500-future-returns-decade-forecast-goldman-sachs-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGoldman%20Sachs%3C%2Fa%3E%20said%20in%20October%20that%20the%20S%26amp%3BP%20500%20would%20return%203%25%20annually%2C%20on%20average%2C%20over%20the%20next%2010%20years%2C%20underperforming%20current%2010-year%20Treasury%20yields.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faffiliate.insider.com%3Fh%3D46c2a992f4fadc8f29c6c60c3c5cfd52e65b120ede09383837dc6b34735f0622%26postID%3D67251eb1d057d3e5c5bf2ffa%26postSlug%3Dstock-market-crash-why-sp500-decade-weak-returns-goldman-jpmorgan-2024-11%26site%3Dbi%26u%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fwww.morningstar.com%252Fnews%252Fmarketwatch%252F20240917123%252Finvestors-should-brace-for-lower-stock-market-returns-over-the-next-decade-jpmorgan-warns%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EJPMorgan%3C%2Fa%3E%20said%20in%20September%20it%20sees%20potential%205.7%25%20annualized%20returns%20over%20that%20span.%20And%20Bank%20of%20America%20said%20the%20index%20would%20return%201-2%25%20a%20year%2C%20but%20that%20dividends%20should%20boost%20that%20number%20significantly.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20not%20every%20day%20that%20these%20institutions%20express%20less-than-bullish%20views%2C%20if%20you%20want%20to%20characterize%20them%20like%20that%2C%20and%20so%20the%20recent%20research%20notes%20caught%20investors'%20attention.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELance%20Roberts%2C%20the%20chief%20investment%20strategist%20at%20RIA%20Advisors%2C%20said%20he%20received%20%26quot%3Bnumerous%26quot%3B%20emails%20about%20the%20Goldman%20and%20JPMorgan%20views%20in%20particular%20and%20set%20out%20to%20address%20the%20claims%20himself%20in%20an%20October%2025%20note.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHis%20conclusion%3F%20The%20banks%20are%20right.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBased%20on%20where%20valuations%20currently%20sit%2C%20it's%20mathematically%20likely%20that%20average%20returns%20are%20muted%20over%20the%20next%2010%20years%2C%20Roberts%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHere%20is%20the%20Shiller%20cyclically-adjusted%20price-to-earnings%20ratio%2C%20which%20is%20a%2010-year%20rolling%20average%20of%20trailing%2012-month%20PE%20ratios.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221242%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22shiller%20cape%20ratio%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F672539f7a0a0cc14f2259a3e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22943%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EGuruFocus.com%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20here's%20the%20relationship%20between%20starting%20valuations%20and%20returns%20over%20the%20subsequent%20decade.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22799%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22cape%20ratio%20and%20forward%2010%20year%20returns%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67253a2401ea6d83dee5bc3b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22461%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3ERIA%20Advisors%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EGoldman%20laid%20this%20out%20another%20way%2C%20illustrating%20this%20close%20relationship.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22882%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22cape%20ratio%20and%20forward%20returns%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67253b309b3250dbbcebc58c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22613%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EGoldman%20Sachs%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20is%20little%20argument%20that%20U.S.%20stock%20market%20valuations%20are%20elevated%20compared%20to%20historical%20averages.%20The%20S%26amp%3BP%20500's%20cyclically%20adjusted%20price-to-earnings%20(CAPE)%20ratio%20remains%20well%20above%20its%20long-term%20exponential%20growth%20trend%2C%26quot%3B%20Roberts%20said%20in%20the%20note.%20%26quot%3BHigh%20valuations%20reflect%20optimism%20but%20can%20also%20signal%20caution.%20If%20the%20market%20is%20pricing%20in%20perfection%2C%20any%20disappointment%20can%20lead%20to%20significant%20corrections.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERoberts%20warned%20investors%20not%20to%20fall%20prey%20to%20a%20recency%20bias%20amid%20ongoing%20strong%20returns%20and%20disregard%20the%20high%20probability%20of%20poor%20returns%20in%20the%20next%2010%20years%20%E2%80%94%20at%20least%20relative%20to%20risk-free%20Treasurys%20and%20the%20market%20returns%20of%20the%20last%2015%20years.%20He%20also%20said%20that%20factors%20like%20less%20dovish%20central%20banks%20and%20potentially%20higher%20inflation%20could%20make%20returns%20less%20attractive%20than%20they've%20been%20in%20the%20last%20few%20decades.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERoberts'%20valuation%20argument%20applies%20most%20to%20investors%20looking%20to%20buy%20now%2C%20not%20necessarily%20those%20who%20have%20held%20positions%20for%20years%20and%20plan%20to%20hold%20them%20for%20decades%20to%20come.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20it's%20important%20to%20remember%20these%20return%20forecasts%20are%20averages%2C%20and%20that%20there%20will%20be%20up%20and%20down%20years%2C%20Roberts%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22800%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22average%20return%20vs%20annual%20percentage%20return%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67253b6aa0a0cc14f2259ac5%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22462%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3ERIA%20Advisors%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20that%20down%20period%20will%20come%20and%20what%20will%20trigger%20it%20remains%20to%20be%20seen.%20Inflation%20has%20cooled%20off%20for%20now%2C%20and%20the%20unemployment%20rate%20has%20stayed%20steady%2C%20hovering%20just%20above%204%25.%20The%20October%20payrolls%20report%20released%20on%20Friday%20by%20the%20Bureau%20of%20Labor%20Statistics%20did%20show%20extremely%20weak%20job%20growth%2C%20but%20strikes%20and%20hurricanes%20are%20believed%20to%20have%20had%20an%20effect%20on%20the%20headline%20number.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTake%20these%20figures%20with%20a%20large%20helping%20of%20salt%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Sam%20Kuhn%2C%20a%20labor%20economist%20at%20recruitment%20platform%20Appcast%2C%20in%20an%20email%20on%20Friday.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInvestors%20appeared%20to%20do%20that%2C%20with%20the%20S%26amp%3BP%20500%20rising%200.4%25%20on%20Friday%20to%205%2C728%2C%202.3%25%20below%20all-time%20highs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20some%20signs%20of%20deterioration%20in%20the%20job%20market%20like%20downward%20payroll%20revisions%20and%20falling%20job%20openings%20and%20hires%2C%20but%20further%20Fed%20rate%20cuts%20are%20expected%20in%20an%20effort%20to%20stimulate%20the%20economy%20and%20avoid%20falling%20into%20a%20recession.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhether%20or%20not%20they%20work%20is%20still%20an%20open%20question%2C%20but%20disruptive%20forces%20always%20come%20along%20at%20one%20point%20or%20another%2C%20Roberts%20reminded%20investors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20will%20be%20fantastic%20bull%20market%20runs%2C%20as%20we%20have%20witnessed%20over%20the%20last%20decade%2C%20but%20to%20experience%20the%20ups%2C%20you%20will%20have%20to%20deal%20with%20the%20eventual%20downs%2C%26quot%3B%20Roberts%20said.%20%26quot%3BDespite%20the%20hopes%20of%20many%2C%20no%20one%20can%20repeal%20the%20cycles%20of%20the%20market%20and%20the%20economy.%20While%20artificial%20interventions%20can%20delay%20and%20extend%20the%20cycles%2C%20the%20reversion%20will%20eventually%20come.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstock-market-crash-why-sp500-decade-weak-returns-goldman-jpmorgan-2024-11%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1730538002000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F655691504ca513d8242b12a0%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstock-market-crash-why-sp500-decade-weak-returns-goldman-jpmorgan-2024-11%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%26quot%3BIf%20the%20market%20is%20pricing%20in%20perfection%2C%20any%20disappointment%20can%20lead%20to%20significant%20corrections%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Lance%20Roberts.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22wedwards%40businessinsider.com%20(William%20Edwards)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A15%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstock-market-crash-why-sp500-decade-weak-returns-goldman-jpmorgan-2024-11%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Shark%20attacks%20surfer%2C%2061%2C%20in%20Hawaii%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1730538000000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fe3.365dm.com%2F24%2F11%2F192