2%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%2215%20Billion%20Miles%20Away%2C%20NASA's%20Voyager%201%20Comes%20Back%20To%20Life%20Using%201981%20Tech%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3ENASA's%2047-year-old%20Voyager%201%20spacecraft%20recently%20established%20contact%20with%20Earth%20after%20a%20brief%20halt%20with%20the%20help%20of%20a%20radio%20transmitter%20that%20has%20not%20been%20used%20since%201981.%20NASA%20engineers%20at%20Jet%20Propulsion%20Laboratory%20(JPL)%20in%20California%20re-established%20contact%20with%20the%20spacecraft%20on%20October%2024.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20spacecraft%2C%20which%20is%20in%20interstellar%20space%20over%2015%20billion%20miles%20away%2C%20experienced%20a%20brief%20interruption%20in%20communication%20on%20October%2016%20due%20to%20a%20shutdown%20of%20one%20of%20its%20transmitters.%20This%20shutdown%20was%20likely%20triggered%20by%20the%20spacecraft's%20fault%20protection%20system%2C%20which%20powers%20down%20certain%20systems%20when%20power%20usage%20is%20too%20high.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20NASA%2C%20a%20message%20takes%20around%2023%20hours%20to%20travel%20one%20way%20-%20from%20Earth%20to%20Voyager%201%20and%20vice-versa.%20On%20October%2016%2C%20when%20the%20NASA%20engineers%20sent%20a%20command%20to%20the%20spacecraft%2C%20they%20could%20not%20detect%20its%20response%20till%20October%2018.%20A%20day%20later%2C%20communication%20with%20Voyager%201%20stopped%20completely.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20an%20investigation%2C%20the%20space%20agency%20team%20discovered%20that%20Voyager%201's%20fault%20protection%20system%20had%20switched%20the%20spacecraft%20to%20a%20second%2C%20lower-power%20transmitter.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EVoyager%201%20has%20two%20radio%20transmitters%2C%20but%20has%20been%20using%20only%20one%20for%20years%20called%20an%20'X-band'.%20However%2C%20the%20other%20transmitter%20-%20the%20'S-band'%20-%20uses%20a%20different%20frequency%20which%20has%20not%20been%20employed%20since%201981.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPresently%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fscience%2Fnasa-identifies-9-potential-landing-sites-for-artemis-iii-mission-near-moon-s-south-pole-6915265%5C%22%3ENASA%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20opted%20to%20avoid%20switching%20back%20to%20the%20X-band%20transmitter%20until%20they%20can%20determine%20what%20activated%20the%20fault%20protection%20system%20-%20which%20may%20take%20weeks.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEngineers%20are%20being%20cautious%20because%20they%20want%20to%20determine%20whether%20there%20are%20any%20potential%20risks%20to%20turning%20on%20the%20X-band.%20In%20the%20meantime%2C%20engineers%20sent%20a%20message%20to%20Voyager%201%20on%20October%2022%20to%20check%20that%20the%20S-band%20transmitter%20was%20working%20and%20received%20confirmation%20on%20October%2024.%20But%20it's%20not%20a%20fix%20the%20team%20wants%20to%20rely%20on%20for%20too%20long%2C%26quot%3B%20Voyager%20mission%20assurance%20manager%2C%20Bruce%20Waggoner%20told%20CNN.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EVoyager%201%20was%20launched%20after%20Voyager%202%2C%20but%20because%20of%20a%20faster%20route%20it%20exited%20the%20asteroid%20belt%20earlier%20than%20its%20twin%2C%20and%20it%20overtook%20Voyager%202%20on%20December%2015%2C%201977.%20The%20spacecraft%20is%20the%20first%20human-made%20object%20to%20venture%20into%20interstellar%20space.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20spacecraft%20was%20the%20first%20to%20cross%20the%20heliosphere%20-%20the%20boundary%20where%20the%20influences%20from%20outside%20our%20solar%20system%20are%20stronger%20than%20those%20from%20the%20Sun.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESo%20far%2C%20the%20Voyager%201%20has%20discovered%20a%20thin%20ring%20around%20Jupiter%20and%20two%20new%20Jovian%20moons%20-%20Thebe%20and%20Metis.%20It%20also%20found%20five%20new%20moons%20and%20a%20new%20ring%20called%20'G-Ring'%20at%20Saturn.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1730524440000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-11%2F7jj78hl_voyager-1-nasa_625x300_02_November_24